{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Required patient fields are validated before downstream processing; missing fields return a clear list of all missing items.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The key failure is at the module boundary: validation must gate the orchestrator so downstream insurance/triage/scheduling are not invoked. A unit test of only the validator can miss that handoff bug.","test_description":"Run intake orchestration with a submission missing `name` and `insurance_id`; assert response includes both missing fields, and assert downstream modules were not executed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Date of birth validation rejects future dates, dates older than 150 years, and non-date strings.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is pure validation logic at a single function/object boundary with no required I/O or cross-module interaction.","test_description":"Table-driven tests for DOB parser/validator with valid DOB, future date, >150-year-old date, and malformed string inputs; assert exact validation outcomes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Insurance eligibility check sends correct patient ID and plan code to payer API and interprets `eligible` / `not eligible` / `pending`.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The behavior crosses a real HTTP/external API boundary. Mocking can hide serialization, request-shape, auth/header, or response-contract mismatches that only appear against the real payer endpoint.","test_description":"Execute eligibility check against payer sandbox API using a known test patient/plan set; verify outbound payload fields and verify system maps each payer status to internal status correctly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"If payer API is unreachable, eligibility is marked `pending` and intake continues.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure mode depends on real network/subprocess behavior (timeouts, DNS/connect failures). Mocked exceptions may miss retry/time-budget behavior and continuation semantics under true outage conditions.","test_description":"Point payer endpoint to an unreachable host or block network route in test environment; run intake and assert eligibility=`pending`, pipeline proceeds to later steps, and no hard failure is returned.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"AI symptom triage assigns high urgency to emergency symptom combinations (e.g., chest pain + shortness of breath).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model judgment quality/non-deterministic outputs, not just deterministic code wiring.","test_description":"Run repeated triage calls on emergency symptom cases against the real triage model; assert high-urgency classification meets an acceptance threshold across runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.12}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Symptom triage outputs a clinician-reviewable natural-language explanation, not only a numeric score.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"If explanation text is model-produced, adequacy and format depend on real LLM output behavior. Mock text would hide real generation failures.","test_description":"Call real triage model with representative symptoms; assert response includes a non-empty explanatory narrative meeting mini